00:14:17,232 --> 00:14:19,151
Baby, l was being a walrus.

236
00:14:19,234 --> 00:14:23,614
JD's not only your friend
but a patient too, and he's scared.

237
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:28,160
Kelso is pushing your buttons.
Every now and then let something go.

238
00:14:28,243 --> 00:14:32,247
Turk's not that mature. He spent
all yesterday being a walrus.

239
00:14:32,331 --> 00:14:34,666
He had straws and stuff...

240
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:38,086
The only thing
JD's scared of is sharks.

241
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:42,341
And he has a weird thing with pennies.
He's not scared about this.

242
00:14:42,424 --> 00:14:47,554
Kelso's not just some harmless
guy pushing my buttons, Carla.

243
00:14:47,638 --> 00:14:48,972
He's a pod person.

244
00:14:49,056 --> 00:14:51,600
- You're wrong.
- You're so wrong.

245
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:54,811
<i>Wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong</i>

246
00:14:58,023 --> 00:15:00,859
<i>You're wrong.</i>

247
00:15:04,029 --> 00:15:07,533
l think you're right. l don't know
how to connect with patients.

248
00:15:07,616 --> 00:15:12,246
Start by touching them, holding
their hand, or stroking their hair,

249
00:15:12,329 --> 00:15:14,540
or give them
a reassuring pat on the arm.

250
00:15:14,623 --> 00:15:18,293
- What are you doing?
- Nothing. You'll be great.

251
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:23,215
Darn right.

252
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,885
There you go, sir.

253
00:15:31,265 --> 00:15:33,892
l'm sorry. lt's my watch, l'll get it.

254
00:15:45,696 --> 00:15:48,490
l'm so sorry. Let me...

255
00:15:55,831 --> 00:16:01,211
Dave, at Sacred Heart we don't
treat symptoms, we treat people.

256
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:04,590
- There's something on your back.
- What does this one say?

257
00:16:04,673 --> 00:16:07,634
''Never stop kicking me.''

258
00:16:07,718 --> 00:16:12,097
And on the other side
is my discharge form.

259
00:16:12,181 --> 00:16:16,727
Bob, you tried to discharge me
an hour before l almost died?

260
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,228
Well...

261
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:22,816
How very clever.

262
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:25,235
What? lt wasn't me. ln fact...

263
00:16:25,319 --> 00:16:28,906
l think you put it there
yourself to get more attention.

264
00:16:33,118 --> 00:16:36,205
lt was me. l put it there.

265
00:16:40,459 --> 00:16:44,505
Hey, buddy. OK,
forget about everything that's going on.

266
00:16:44,588 --> 00:16:48,467
We know that you're bummed out
about missing Thanksgiving so...

267
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:51,094
we decided to bring it to you.

268
00:16:51,178 --> 00:16:54,723
Wow, guys, thanks.
Where's the food?

269
00:16:59,853 --> 00:17:02,940
Who wants the unmentionables?

270
00:17:05,067 --> 00:17:07,945
Bambi? Your fever's spiking.

271
00:17:08,028 --> 00:17:12,366
They're worried your appendix might
burst so we're going into surgery now.

272
00:17:12,449 --> 00:17:13,659
Who's on call?

273
00:17:13,742 --> 00:17:16,620
Dr Turk, let's get started.

274
00:17:24,127 --> 00:17:28,006
<i>Most doctors don't believe in
the out-of-body experience thing,</i>

275
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:30,300
<i>and I don't know
if it was real or a dream,</i>

276
00:17:30,384 --> 00:17:34,012
<i>but I swear I was up there
watching Turk operate on me.</i>

277
00:17:34,096 --> 00:17:37,307
<i>And I have to say,
he's an amazing surgeon.</i>

278
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:42,104
Dude, could you not look over
my shoulder while l'm doing this?

279
00:17:42,187 --> 00:17:44,022
lt's a little unnerving.

280
00:17:44,106 --> 00:17:48,861
You've got a little fever.
Probably atelectasis from lying in bed.

281
00:17:48,944 --> 00:17:51,822
- l'm really uncomfortable.
- l'm so sorry.

282
00:17:51,905 --> 00:17:55,993
- You're not gonna hug me, are you?
- l'm done with all that.

283
00:17:56,076 --> 00:17:59,788
lf it makes you feel better,
l hate this touchy-feely culture.

284
00:17:59,872 --> 00:18:00,998
Thank you.

285
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:03,542
That whole ''kiss hello'' thing.

286
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:06,420
l don't want anyone touching me
unless we have sex.

287
00:18:06,503 --> 00:18:08,714
Even then l don't want them
to overdo it.

288
00:18:08,797 --> 00:18:11,884
- Where in Connecticut are you from?
- Greenwich. You?

289
00:18:11,967 --> 00:18:15,596
Darien.
l'm really burning up here.

290
00:18:18,098 --> 00:18:21,518
God, that's fantastic.
lt's like an ice pack.

291
00:18:21,602 --> 00:18:22,895
Yeah.

292
00:18:24,563 --> 00:18:28,483
l'm sorry to hear about your mom.
Are you at least close with your dad?

293
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:32,529
You see this right here?
That's his work.

294
00:18:32,613 --> 00:18:35,365
Pretty good for a man
in a wheelchair.

295
00:18:35,449 --> 00:18:38,660
Doc, l'm sorry you gotta be here
on Thanksgiving night.

296
00:18:38,744 --> 00:18:42,623
My wife can't cook anyway, she's 22.
What are you doing?

297
00:18:42,706 --> 00:18:46,335
Forget about me. What's your wife
look like? Any pictures?

298
00:18:46,418 --> 00:18:48,587
Not of this one.

299
00:18:48,670 --> 00:18:51,298
You know, being back at this old place,

300
00:18:51,381 --> 00:18:54,718
you know the thing l have found
to be the most disappointing?

301
00:18:54,801 --> 00:18:56,053
l think l can guess.

302
00:18:56,136 --> 00:18:58,263
You.

303
00:18:59,306 --> 00:19:03,602
Probably because you do things
like show up the Chief of Medicine,

304
00:19:03,685 --> 00:19:07,272
when anybody who's been in a room
with Bob Kelso for two minutes

305
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:08,857
knows how big an ass he is.

306
00:19:08,941 --> 00:19:13,737
- Go easy, l just thought...
- You don't think, Perry.

307
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:16,448
You're such a talented doctor.

308
00:19:16,532 --> 00:19:21,703
lf you played the game you'd be in
a position to change things around here.

309
00:19:21,787 --> 00:19:25,624
But you're too stubborn for that,
aren't you?

310
00:19:28,335 --> 00:19:30,087
All right, kid.

311
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:32,714
Gin. Your deal.

312
00:19:46,311 --> 00:19:49,565
Hi. l just need to
check on your incision.

313
00:19:49,648 --> 00:19:51,859
- Turk, l was an idiot.
- lt's OK, man.

314
00:19:51,942 --> 00:19:56,196
No, seriously, man. l want you to know,
if l ever need surgery again,

315
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,781
l want you inside of me.

316
00:19:57,865 --> 00:19:59,992
l want to be the one inside of you.

317
00:20:04,538 --> 00:20:06,582
Look, JD, l get it.

318
00:20:08,208 --> 00:20:12,421
To me you'll always be that geeky kid
with the Pat Benatar t-shirt.

319
00:20:12,504 --> 00:20:14,047
Dude, she rocks.

320
00:20:15,966 --> 00:20:18,969
l want you to know
how serious l am about what l do.

321
00:20:19,052 --> 00:20:21,346
Did you stitch your initials into me?

322
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:26,185
That's not important. lt's still
Thanksgiving for 20 more minutes.

323
00:20:28,228 --> 00:20:30,814
Now, you can have ginger ale

324
00:20:30,898 --> 00:20:33,442
and a cracker.

325
00:20:34,818 --> 00:20:38,030
l forgot. Your change. Two pennies.

326
00:20:38,113 --> 00:20:40,949
Get those pennies away from me.

327
00:20:41,325 --> 00:20:43,452
Happy Thanksgiving, man.

328
00:20:43,535 --> 00:20:45,537
<i>I guess what they say is true.</i>

329
00:20:45,621 --> 00:20:48,624
<i>The people you work with
